betterquesting:10.desc:8: Necessary to avoid coal poisoning. Right-click on a cloth rag to make a piss-stained rag.
The earliest (useful) reactor. Creates power and decays rods. Will explode if you don't provide coolant.
Manufactures various circuits. Is required for every machine after this.
Creates everything!
Essential for crafting basic machines. Can be upgraded using more advanced materials.
Craft a blank stamp, and use the machine template folder to convert it into a plate stamp.
Manually mining for oil is okay, but horribly inefficient. Plus, you have better things to do.
Now you're making all this steam, you have to put it somewhere.
Honestly I don't know how to use OR logic. Same as the other quest.
Allows simpler manufacturing of common materials and allows for the creation of more advanced machinery.
The most basic way to make plates, wires, and circuit wafers. Essential for early progression. Can be replaced by electric and conveyor press later.
Steel is the backbone of this modpack. You will need a lot of it. Craft a blast furnace and input iron, coal, and fuel to create steel.

The burner press and blast furnace, while useful, are not very efficient. This can be alleviated by placing a blast furnace extension above the blast furnace, and a burner press preheater underneath the press.
Used to grind minerals and mineralloids into powder.
The simplest method of creating power. Requires cables or wires to connect to machines that require power.
Used to cast and mix alloys. Place on top of the heating oven and add fuel to produce heat.
Decent armour for early game, and can be upgraded later. Does not help with radiation.
Contains boron, cobalt, zirconium, and niobium, all of which are useful for nuclear activities.
Piss in a rag can only protect you from so much.
Extremely necessary component for synthesising any unnaturally-occuring substance. Requires power.
If you plan on making anything with your assembly machine, you'll need this.
Water pumps are hard to justify in the early game, consider infinite water instead! Although slower, it is much easier logistically to plop one of these into any barrel or machine.
The ZIRNOX requires carbon dioxide to function. It does not decay over time, and only needs to be put in once. Not doing this will make your ZIRNOX explode violently.
Durable steel alloy strengthened by cobalt. Used to manufacture machinery. Requires alloying template for the crucible.
Necessary to add gas mask filters, cladding, PLSS, or other upgrades to your equipment.
Stepping stone to not instantly being vaporised by a demon core.
It goes up, it goes down. Place in a kerosene container to charge.
No Description
No Description
Still can't pick up the demon core...
Welcome to mid-game radiation resistance! You can lug around uranium as you please, and can discover new and horrific forms of radiation sickness!
The peak of cladding. Probably don't touch the demon core unless you have a Liquidator suit anyway.
Potentially useful if your gear is dropped in a warzone.
Insanely useful in the early game for crucible components, heating ovens, and the blast furnace.
Useful for creating dead dirt to grow mustard plants on.
Made by trading stuff to kobolds. I don't know what stuff yet, but I'll find out one day. Prerequisite for the M1TTY Environmental Suit
Perfect for building. Lets you hover.
Great upgrade for long-distance travel.
Greatly increased horizontal speed. Requires BF Rocket Fuel.
The beginning of the pack! As far as I'm aware...
Used for adding blood to the altar. Do note that it's your own blood, so try not to kill yourself.
Once you've bled over the altar a bit, toss in a diamond to make a weak blood gem. This is used to craft everything else in the modpack, as far as I'm aware.
Very useful for crafting stuff. Uses blood orbs.
Occasionally useful
The place where all the magic happens. Metaphorically.
Infinite water for cooking.
Holds stuff for cooking. Can be made a double fridge by placing another on top.
Cooks food. Needs fuel. What more can be said?
Craft a full hazmat suit.
Basic safety gear is not enough.
Recommended for general-purpose nuclear activities.
Heats up oil or water. Explodes if it gets too full.
Refines crude oil into lots of good stuff.
Put hot oil in a refinery to manufacture petroleum gas. Then add coal powder and fluorite to create polymer.
Increases metal output from ores.
Acquired via nuclear irradiation or centrifuging uranium hexafluoride.
Base isotope for radioactive shenanigans. Is dug out of the ground.
Used to create the Tier 4 Anvil, and allows for manufacture of advanced machines.
Used to auto-craft wire.
Crucial for Tier 3 Anvils, and unbreakable tools. Essential for creating advanced materials.
Can be extracted via fish oil, from cinnabar or from red mud. Necessary to produce Desh.
Tier 3 Anvil, needed to progress.
Cracks crude oil, which can be refined into various products, most importantly rubber.
Use unsaturated hydrocarbons to create rubber! You are going to need A LOT of this.
You're going to want to tell how irradiated you are if you don't like exploding violently.
Make machines work faster, albeit with greater power use.
Conductive material used in wiring and machinery.
Cheaply connects and provides power to machines.
Connects machines over longer distances. Can be installed with or without transformers.
It's HUGE! Requires substation to transfer power into or out of it, but not between giant pylons.
Turns water into steam while the sun is out. Free power, but not as good as nuclear power you get later on.
Turns steam into power and low-pressure steam. LP Steam can be drained into the atmosphere or condensed back into water.
Turns Low-Pressure Steam back into water, allowing closed-loop systems.
Can store cold, non-corrosive liquids (Mostly water).
Can hold hot fluids, such as steam. Will corrode if hazardous fluids are placed within.
Can hold most things, except antimatter and highly corrosive materials. The standard for most purposes.
Like an oven, but witcherier.
Makes brews and balls.
Holds equipment for use in a multi-block kitchen.
You don't want to be eating raw food forever, do you?
Most boring part of the modpack, also the most fun.
Ka-boom!
Space!
Not environmentally friendly, but necessary for the production of rubber, plastic, and rocket fuel.
Early game resource collection boon!
empty until i use the mod
empty until i use the mod
You aren't going to survive very long unprotected. Better get some upgrades, too. Base armour is not nearly strong enough for what we're doing.
Necessary to live.
Being in endgame does not mean you're at the end.
